  "prompt": "How much do astrophysicists make at NASA?",
  "response": "The salary of astrophysicists at NASA can vary widely based on factors such as experience, education, and position level. As of my last update, entry-level astrophysicists or science researchers at NASA may earn a salary in the range of $60,000 to $90,000 per year. Mid-level professionals with several years of experience can earn between $90,000 and $120,000, while senior scientists or researchers may make upwards of $120,000 to $150,000 or more annually.\n\nAdditionally, NASA's salary structure is often influenced by the federal government's General Schedule (GS) pay scale. The specific pay grade and step assigned to an individual can significantly affect their salary. \n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it is best to consult official NASA job postings or federal employment resources.",
